      "writtenOn": "2026-04-27T15:51:48Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Thank you for the review. I understand the security concern regarding session hijacking and privilege escalation through Set Channel Security Keys.\n\nSince this command is defined in the IPMI v2.0 specification (Table 22-30), are there any OpenBMC guidelines or precedents for excluding optional but spec-defined commands on security grounds? Understanding this would help me align future contributions accordingly.",
      "parentUuid": "99c9b5bf_f9436bb5",
      "revId": "631b5760045c44027bb4e246c6c0b67da66c6c3e",
      "serverId": "adbd0a64-1f21-4d83-b585-671fe73cb6e4"
    },
    {
      "unresolved": true,
